description:
Standing before the Diet of Worms, Martin Luther refused to go against his conscience and famously said, Here I stand, I can do no other. So, help me God. Despite his relatively young age and lack of experience, we see that Martin Luther was not swayed by pressure or opinion. He had bravely proceeded the Reformation with the belief that the bible was the foundation of all christian belief and practice.

To find out more information about Martin Luther read our extended article.
